# Email Sending

Vercel serverless functions block outbound SMTP (ports 25, 465, 587). Always use Resend (HTTP API).

## Pattern

```ts
import { Resend } from 'resend';
const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY);
await resend.emails.send({ from, to, replyTo, subject, html });
```

## Config
- Env var: `RESEND_API_KEY` (set in Vercel dashboard and .env.local)
- `from`: `'Al-Amir Islamic Center <onboarding@resend.dev>'` until domain `alamiric.org` is verified in Resend
- `to`: always `['info@alamiric.org']`
- `replyTo`: visitor's email from the form (so replies go back to them)

## After domain verification
Change `from` to `'Al-Amir Islamic Center <info@alamiric.org>'`
